# Algorithm and Data Flow

## Status algorithm

Use `algorithm.DetermineStatus` as the single status decision path

Expected inputs:

- recent user report count
- report baseline for current hour-of-week bucket
- recent probe totals and failures
- probe baseline when available

Current behavior includes:

- cold start guardrails for low baseline history
- z-score based report anomaly checks for mature baselines
- probe failure-rate checks with fallback thresholds

## API request flow

- `/api/services` and `/api/services/search`
    - fetch base service rows
    - batch load baselines for current hour bucket
    - batch load recent probe stats
    - compute status per row
- `/api/service/:slug`
    - fetch one service
    - fetch report count, baseline, probe stats
    - compute status for detail card

## Worker flow

- baseline worker
    - recomputes baseline buckets periodically
- incident worker
    - recomputes current status for active services
    - opens incident on transition to issues
    - resolves incident on transition to operational

## Probe optionality requirement

Do not make probe data mandatory

- missing probe rows or probe schema availability should not break status pages
- fall back to report-only signals when probe data is missing
